The paper also mentions genetic programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Markov chains and stationary distributions suggests a connection to machine learning and probabilistic modeling (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the need for a structured design methodology, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses theoretical advances, which could involve algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
